    <h2 class="date-header">November 25, 2012</h2>

	<div class="entry-category-blogging entry-author-crof entry-type-post entry" id="entry-6a00d83451bd6d69e2017c33fb425a970b">
       <div class="entry-inner">
					<h3 class="entry-header"><a href="https://crofsblogs.typepad.com/ckbetas/2012/11/le-blog-de-jean-paul-sartre.html">Le Blog de Jean-Paul Sartre</a></h3>
		



		<div class="entry-content">

			<div class="entry-body">
				You really need to have grown up when Sartre was in full cry to appreciate it, but this <em>New Yorker</em> piece is still pretty funny:&#0160;<a href="https://www.newyorker.com/online/blogs/shouts/2012/10/le-blog-de-jean-paul-sartre.html" title="Jean-Paul Sartre&#39;s Blog : The New Yorker">Jean-Paul Sartre&#39;s Blog</a>. The first post:
<blockquote cite="http://www.newyorker.com/online/blogs/shouts/2012/10/le-blog-de-jean-paul-sartre.html"><strong>Saturday, 11 July, 1959: 2:07 A.M.&#0160;
</strong></blockquote>
<blockquote cite="http://www.newyorker.com/online/blogs/shouts/2012/10/le-blog-de-jean-paul-sartre.html">I am awake and alone at 2 A.M.&#0160;
</blockquote>
<blockquote cite="http://www.newyorker.com/online/blogs/shouts/2012/10/le-blog-de-jean-paul-sartre.html">There must be a God. There cannot be a God.&#0160;</blockquote>
<blockquote cite="http://www.newyorker.com/online/blogs/shouts/2012/10/le-blog-de-jean-paul-sartre.html">I will start a blog.</blockquote>
			</div>
			


