    <h2 class="date-header">October 16, 2012</h2>

	<div class="entry-category-blogging entry-category-webwriting entry-author-crof entry-type-post entry" id="entry-6a00d83451bd6d69e2017ee43636f9970d">
       <div class="entry-inner">
					<h3 class="entry-header"><a href="https://crofsblogs.typepad.com/ckbetas/2012/10/medicine-in-the-media-2012.html">Medicine in the Media 2012</a></h3>
		



		<div class="entry-content">

			<div class="entry-body">
				Thanks to <a href="https://twitter.com/marynmck" target="_blank">Maryn McKenna</a> for tweeting the link to this. Via Tumblr, Scott Hensley of NPR&#39;s Shots blog offers a 24-page presentation on writing for the web, delivered at&#0160;<a href="http://medicineinthemedia.tumblr.com/" title="Medicine in the Media 2012">Medicine in the Media 2012</a>. While he focuses on medical reporting, much of what he says applies to webwriting in general.
			</div>
			


<!-- SIGNATURE -->




			
		</div>
